[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing Kotlin scripting metadata**\n\nI’m considering the library I'm testing, which is kotlin-scripting-jvm. I’m wondering if it relies on transitive kotlin-scripting-common metadata for ScriptCompilationConfiguration, but it provides PropertiesCollection instead. I question if the metadata repository applies to all coordinates on the classpath. Yes, it seems to, but for exact mode, the library class requires metadata. Maybe the common metadata is already there, but not explicitly in the script compilation context.\n\n**Considering metadata and testing**\n\nI'm thinking about adding metadata now, but my main objective is refining tests to reach uncovered call sites instead of just fixing metadata. The rules say tests should execute under Native Image, so I need to ensure the metadata is properly generated. I might manually add minimal metadata, but there’s a risk of it being too broad. Maybe I can catch errors to avoid deserialization issues, but it seems I need to figure out the exact serialization metadata for the classes involved.\n\n**Analyzing metadata for transitive types**\n\nI'm considering that for transitive common types, the metadata should belong to a common artifact. Maybe I should update the common metadata, but I need to be cautious about broadly patching it since the task is actively coordinating. However, if metadata is missing, it should exist in common. Tests for scripting-jvm can use the common metadata repository, but if ScriptCompilationConfiguration/KotlinType is absent, native fails. I'm also wondering if the kotlin-scripting-common metadata includes everything needed, but it seems only partial.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0879ef3d4eccd5020169f903a55ee0819799fc781f0140ff2b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-QO5dzipoQTkdHDt_x9ElEwBxGS-Pl4-4hAqL8RRnga9HXzJ5dTl5Ow-ctQArnrWCUZG5JoKB8ZjLNMunJEf8vCJAx_D